                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the UI and graphical enhancements are alot more useful then the stat boosts.
<br />
For us DMA is god, for alot of classes HoTT is really great (knight that sees the mob's on a healer/caster and not the warrior so goes for agro, druid that notices the mob he was nuking switches target so starts a spot heal, even if no hp dmg done yet, tank knowing who is his mob's target all the time, etc), I started to like NPC health ( dont need to target mob while doing cc, just glance at the name), Spell awareness is obviously good (not only to see what mobs cast, but also your group/raid), etc. 
<br />

<br />
Those abilities all outweight a bit of mana/hp/atk imo and I'm definitely buying them before the stat boosts (got DMA so far saving for HoTT).
<br />

<br />
P.S. You do get leader AA for being group leader in a raid and it seems like leader AA comes really fast on raids, so sneak into those group leader spots  <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7110&alt=136431" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jennifer DeGartes</a>, Enchantress of <a href="http://www.vazaelle.dk" target="_blank" class="postlink">Caer Cadarn</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
