                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Got my cleric Designate MA last night.  That ability rocks.  You know which one the MT is going for.  This would be the first one I recommend any chanter go for.  
<br />

<br />
She also has NPC Health.  Without Designate MA, just a nice parlor trick that means you can look at the mob's name to see it's health, no need to check the target box.  With it, it becomes much more useful.  You can, for instance, target your charmed pet, but still see the health of the mob the MA is beating on.
<br />

<br />
Next up is Health of Target's Target.  I want this so that it's easier for the likes of a druid to nuke and know when to pop in a heal.  And also for reasons similiar to the DMA+NPC Health combo, except it won't be tied to the MA's target and I won't have to be looking in that direction to see.  Both useful things.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
